!, 
<collectionCode id="ED18AE499258773AFF76FF12FF4ABC97" box="[136,219,194,220]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15175" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15175" name="Universidade Federal do Paraná" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" type="Herbarium">UPCB</collectionCode>
!); 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9258773AFF0DFF12FE2CBC97" box="[243,445,194,221]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">Jardim, J.G. 5040</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode id="ED18AE499258773AFE32FF12FDBCBC97" box="[460,557,194,220]" country="Brazil" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15526" name="CEPEC, CEPLAC" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" type="Herbarium">CEPEC</collectionCode>
!, 
<collectionCode id="ED18AE499258773AFDC5FF13FDF2BC96" box="[571,611,195,221]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED18AE499258773AFD90FF12FD50BC97" box="[622,705,194,220]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15175" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15175" name="Universidade Federal do Paraná" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" type="Herbarium">UPCB</collectionCode>
!).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB6368C9258773AFF43FF36FC49BD03" blockId="8.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9258773AFF43FF36FE26BD4B" bold="true" box="[189,439,230,256]" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9258773AFE49FF36FD77BD4B" box="[439,742,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9258773AFE2AFF36FD77BD4B" box="[468,742,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustipetala">Bertolonia angustipetala</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has an EOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B699258773AFC6DFF36FC6ABD48" box="[915,1019,230,259]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" unit="km" value="0.01">0.010 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B699258773AFB6BFF36FA91BD48" box="[1173,1280,230,259]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" unit="km" value="0.035">0.035 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Critically Endangered” (CR), following 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D9258773AFD0DFEDAFC1BBD6F" author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[755,906,266,292]" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories. This species has been collected only three times within the “Estação Ecológica Estadual Wenceslau Guimarães”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31365079258773AFF43FE82FD35BE23" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB6368C9258773AFF43FE82FD35BE23" blockId="8.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9258773AFF43FE82FE98BD27" bold="true" box="[189,265,338,364]" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9258773AFED8FE82FDAABD27" box="[294,571,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustipetala">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9258773AFED8FE82FDAABD27" box="[294,571,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">Bertolonia angustipetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E9258773AFD22FE82FCB1BD27" box="[732,800,338,364]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane rainforests (
<figureCitation id="13322A099258773AFB5CFE82FB64BD26" box="[1186,1269,338,365]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[341,1239,654,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-255@5.[340,1247,641,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A. Bertolonia alternifolia. B. Bertolonia angustipetala. C. Bertolonia bullata. D. Bertolonia carmoi. E. Bertolonia cuspidata. F. Bertolonia hirsutissima. G. Bertolonia igrapiuna. H. Bertolonia kollmannii." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597686/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
). Collected with flowers in December and fruits in May and December. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9258773AFD07FEA6FB80BDDB" box="[761,1041,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustipetala">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9258773AFD07FEA6FB80BDDB" box="[761,1041,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">Bertolonia angustipetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the small (3.9–8 × 
<quantity id="4CF19B699258773AFF5EFE4AFEB1BDFE" box="[160,288,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" unit="cm" value="2.75" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="1.8">1.8–3.7 cm</quantity>
) and elliptic leaf blades, these sparsely glandulose-punctate, and linear-lanceolate and apiculate petals. It shares with 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9258773AFED1FE6EFD7FBD93" authority="Bacci &amp; Amorim" authorityName="Bacci &amp; Amorim" box="[303,750,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9258773AFED1FE6EFD8CBD93" box="[303,541,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">Bertolonia cuspidata</emphasis>
Bacci &amp; Amorim
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D9258773AFCE9FE6EFBBDBD93" author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[791,1068,446,473]" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" pagination="767 - 792" refId="ref18533" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2018) Increased Sampling in Under-Collected Areas Sheds New Light on the Diversity and Distribution of Bertolonia, an Atlantic Forest Endemic Genus. Systematic Botany 43 (3): 767 - 792. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 697490" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bacci 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9258773AFC9FFE6FFC04BD93" box="[865,917,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">et al</emphasis>
. (2018: 772)
</bibRefCitation>
the membranaceous, glandulosepunctate leaf blades with entire margins. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9258773AFD32FE32FC72BDB7" box="[716,995,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustipetala">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9258773AFD32FE32FC72BDB7" box="[716,995,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">Bertolonia angustipetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the smaller leaf blades (3.9–8 × 
<quantity id="4CF19B699258773AFF61FDD6FE8EBE6A" box="[159,287,518,545]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" unit="cm" value="2.75" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="1.8">1.8–3.7 cm</quantity>
) with an acute apex (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9258773AFDEFFDD7FDA1BE6B" box="[529,560,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">vs.</emphasis>
bigger leaf blades,7.3–12.2 × 
<quantity id="4CF19B699258773AFC79FDD6FC63BE6A" box="[903,1010,518,545]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.95" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.9" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" unit="cm" value="4.95" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.9">3.9–6 cm</quantity>
, with a cuspidate apex in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9258773AFAE8FDD7FA33BE6B" box="[1302,1442,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9258773AFAE8FDD7FA33BE6B" box="[1302,1442,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">B. cuspidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and linear-lanceolate petals (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9258773AFE2DFDFBFE60BE0F" box="[467,497,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">vs.</emphasis>
elliptic or obovate petals; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D9258773AFCD7FDFAFC65BE0F" author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[809,1012,554,581]" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" pagination="767 - 792" refId="ref18533" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2018) Increased Sampling in Under-Collected Areas Sheds New Light on the Diversity and Distribution of Bertolonia, an Atlantic Forest Endemic Genus. Systematic Botany 43 (3): 767 - 792. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 697490" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bacci 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9258773AFC8CFDFBFC37BE0F" box="[882,934,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). For more details, see notes under 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F9258773AFA6DFDFBFEB1BE23" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustipetala">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9258773AFA6DFDFBFEB1BE23" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">B. angustipetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D9258773AFEBAFD9EFD84BE23" author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[324,533,590,617]" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" pagination="767 - 792" refId="ref18533" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2018) Increased Sampling in Under-Collected Areas Sheds New Light on the Diversity and Distribution of Bertolonia, an Atlantic Forest Endemic Genus. Systematic Botany 43 (3): 767 - 792. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 697490" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bacci 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E9258773AFE75FD9FFE2DBE23" box="[395,444,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation id="C68B03379258773AFDB5FD9EFD0FBE23" box="[587,670,590,616]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" tableUuid="DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
